<TEXT>
the government has decided that hundreds of 
soviet jews seeking asylum in east germany can stay although they 
entered the country with tourist visas rather than the required 
residency permits 
the decision wednesday ends weeks of uncertainty for nearly 400 
soviet jews who have settled in east germany since april 
interior ministry spokesman achim hildebrandt said however 
that the thousands of romanians who have been flooding into east 
germany will be considered for asylum only on a casebycase basis 
east germany now on the threshold of uniting with wealthy west 
germany has turned into a magnet for asylumseekers from other 
eastern european nations facing a bleaker economic future 
</TEXT>
