conditions worsened at the compounds supplies of food and medicine 
are strained and hygienic conditions poor 
the first group of 51 people to leave the country flew to 
czechoslovakia on monday 
albania has resisted the democratic reforms that swept the rest 
of eastern europe last year despite limited restructuring this 
year by communist leader ramiz alia albania remains europes most 
backward and isolated nation 
trying to stem popular discontent the government in the past 
week has replaced highranking officials including several 
hardliners associated with the late communist ruler enver hoxha 
on wednesday more reform was announced 
the state news agency ata said the government would allow some 
privatization of handicrafts and small trade but entrepreneurs 
could not employ nonfamily members and had to register with the 
authorities 
as part of the boatlift the italianchartered ship appia left 
venice on wednesday carrying nine nurses and three doctors from 
the red cross said lino de rosa a director of the company that 
owns the ships 
the frenchchartered ship was carrying 44 french officials 
doctors and 3 tons of medical supplies and food said vomviras it 
was to arrive off durres later today then return with the refugees 
to the french port of marseille 
another vessel the espresso grecia was to leave from the 
southern italian city of brindisi later today de rosa said 
the ships were to wait in durres harbor until the albanians 
decide to let them dock late today or early friday foreign 
ministry officials said 
new arrivals at the embassies have dropped off dramatically 
since police placed a cordon around the embassy quarter this week 
diplomats said 
many of the asylumseekers in tirana have said they eventually 
want to emigrate to the united states which does not have 
diplomatic relations with albania 
in washington state department deputy spokesman richard boucher 
said the united states has no specific quota for albanian refugees 
but has a ceiling of 6500 on refugees from eastern europe so far 
this year 52 albanian refugees have resettled in the united 
states boucher said 
