dr arnold relman said thursday he will retire in 
june after 14 years as editor of the new england journal of 
medicine the worlds leading chronicle of medical research 
relman 67 said he plans to write teach and lecture after he 
retires as editor in chief 
ive been thinking about it for some time and finally 
decided relman said its better to leave a little too soon 
than a little too late 
during relmans tenure the journals circulation grew by 
onethird and the weekly magazine established itself as a forum 
for exploring social and economic issues in medicine as well as 
being the leading showcase of research findings 
relman was frequently criticized for using the journal to 
question among other things the growing role of business in 
medical care 
relman has provided the strongest voice for professionalism 
and against business taking over medicine said dr george 
lundberg editor of the journal of the american medical association 
he has sought controversy in a responsible way he said 
he was very early in those areas and did engender great 
controversy and a lot of personal attacks he stood his ground and 
should have we are all in his debt for doing so 
the new england journal founded in 1812 was already one of the 
worlds leading medical publications when relman took over from dr 
franz ingelfinger in 1977 relman has continued to publish a large 
share of the worlds hottest medical research 
if you look worldwide the new england journal is clearly the 
leading journal of clinical medicine and has been for some time 
said david pendlebury editor of science watch published by the 
institute for scientific information in philadelphia 
many agree that relmans chief accomplishment has been taking 
the journal into the contentious area of medical finance and 
ethics the journal has explored and editorialized about such areas 
as the growth of profitmaking medicine and physicians financial 
conflict of interest 
relman said he plans to concentrate on these and related matters 
after he leaves the journal 
i want to spend the next few years as a more active 
participant in what i think will be a growing national discussion 
of health care he said i think the medical profession can 
make a major contribution toward solving the health care problems 
of this country if it will rouse itself i want to help in that 
process 
dr barry m manuel president of the massachusetts medical 
society which owns the journal said a search committee will be 
established soon to name a new top editor 
while relman has been editor the journals circulation has 
grown from 165000 to 225000 and it claims the largest paid 
circulation of any medical journal in the world 
before joining the new england journal relman taught at boston 
university and the university of pennsylvania and edited the 
journal of clinical investigation 
