court of appeals for the district of columbia which is considering 
a 24hour ban the fcc imposed under orders from congress in 1988 
the court last year told the commission not to enforce the 
24hour ban pending further review but said the commission could 
develop evidence supporting its position 
the fcc report could play a major role in how the appeals court 
and inevitably the supreme court decides the issue 
in essence the fcc is now enforcing the regulations that were 
in effect before congress told the commission two years ago to ban 
indecent programming roundtheclock 
the current regulations ban obscene material at all times and 
indecent material from about 6 am to 8 pm local time the fcc 
defines indecent as language or material that depicts or 
describes in terms patently offensive as measured by contemporary 
community standards for the broadcast medium sexual or excretory 
activities or organs 
neither the current regulation nor a 24hour ban would affect 
cable television programming 
