news of mrs chamorros promise to negotiate a nationwide social 
accord with workers and businessmen on economic reforms 
other concessions include a promise to establish a new national 
minimum wage in september payable in a new currency that will 
trade on a par with the dollar 
the nicaraguan cordoba has been devalued more than 20 times 
since mrs chamorro inherited a bankrupt government and now goes 
for about 450000 to the dollar on the black market 
francisco mayorga the head of the central bank and the 
architect of the governments economic program said he hoped the 
strike had reaffirmed the possibility of cooperation 
we could have arrived at the same outcome without a strike 
without a confrontation without a crisis he said on radio 
catolica 
