<TEXT>
here is the text of the nicaraguan 
strike settlement as translated from spanish by the associated 
press 
1 considering the need to reestablish social tranquility and a 
climate of confidence that is needed to foster reactivation of the 
economy the government of nicaragua represented by the employment 
and salary commission met with a delegation of the national 
workers front fnt july 11 1990 
after a presentation to the government by the labor leaders the 
government of nicaragua communicates the following 
first it has made the following decisions to be effective 
immediately 
it will apply in the present month of july a general 
adjustment of 43 percent to budgeted salaries 
this adjustment will be paid july 25 
at the same time it is established that in the month of august a 
salary increase for the budgeted sector will be established 
according to the economic capacity of the government this 
emphasizes the need to help the majority of the lowestpaid workers 
an environment of confidence and labor stability will be 
strengthened for public servants of the central government 
autonomous organizations and staterun businesses 
all workers who return normally to their jobs will have the 
right to continue in them 
meanwhile the civil service law is changed so that public 
sector workers fired after april 26 1990 will get an indemnity 
equal to a months salary for each year worked up to three months 
cases in which special agreements or arrangements have been reached 
are excepted 
transportation tokens to all workers and students who now get 
them are guaranteed 
the government will pay the debts the transportation and 
construction ministry owes to businesses 
with relation to law 9010 the ministry of agriculture and 
livestock has reviewed all rental requests which were made public 
in separate lists and ended the application of said law as the 
rental contracts contemplate businesses will push for stability 
and more rights for workers on rented productive lands 
reclassification of job categories by the state to take effect 
in september of this year will proceed 
second the following points will be studied and analyzed 
in problems existing in some branches of industry especially 
in textiles construction metals public transport and other 
branches of the economy mining timber fishing etc a program 
will be put in practice requiring industrial reactivation and 
rehabilitation the immediate objective of which will be to 
maintain jobs for the workers in these areas to bring this about a 
mixed commission will be organized among government representatives 
and those of the ftn which will be installed monday july 16 
giving priority to the textile industry 
within the framework of tripartism a commission will be 
formed made up of employers unions and the government to prepare a 
proposal for a minimum wage law that will be presented to the 
national assembly in september at the latest the minimum wage will 
be expressed in gold cordobas 
third the government ratifies entirely its extension of an 
agreement reached with the fnt may 16 1990 which includes 
the application of national agreements with their respective 
additions and rules signed with the education ministry the 
national association of nicaraguan educators and the health 
ministry the federation of health workers and will not change them 
the commitment on regulations for the civil service law any 
modification of this agreement will be discussed in advance and 
approved by the parties 
fourth representatives of the fnt who sign the present 
communique express 
taking into consideration resolutions that the government of 
nicaragua makes public in this communique pledge that the workers 
and employees will return normally to their work july 12 of this 
year they also pledge to respect the normality and public order in 
the entire country 
their willingness to promote the resumption of productive work 
in the agriculture and livestock sector and to reestablish the 
climate of tranquility and labor stability that is required to 
fulfill production goals 
their satisfaction over the governments statements that it 
will take no reprisals against workers and employees who return to 
their jobs normally beginning july 12 
in concluding the conversations which were held in a climate of 
understanding both parties pledge to maintain a fluid and 
permanent communication on the economic problems for the purpose of 
contributing to reactivation of production and national 
reconstruction 
in the city of managua the 11th day of the month of july of 
1990 
signed for the government 
antonio lacayo minister of the presidency 
francisco rosales minister of labor 
silvio de franco minister of the economy 
emilio pereira minister of finances 
francisco mayorga ministerdirector of the central bank of 
nicaragua 
 
for the fnt 
lucio jimenez 
edgardo garcia 
gustavo porras 
guillermo martinez 
jose angel bermudez 
freddy cruz 
lilly soto 
</TEXT>
