a trucker from hopkinsville ky 
the regulation the us labor department proposed wednesday 
would cover 54 million businesses with 35 million workers like 
jerry aiello a 48yearold truck driver from upland calif also 
taking a break at the truck stop 
aiello wears his seat belt when the road gets bumpy but doesnt 
like the way it cuts into his belly on long hauls and he doesnt 
think the government can force him to buckle up 
i dont see how theyre going to enforce it they cant even 
enforce the drug laws said aiello who was hauling lumber on 
