have to wear seat belts selfemployed people and businesses with 
10 or fewer employees would be exempt 
labor secretary elizabeth dole said the new rules could save up 
to 685 lives a year she said automobile accidents were the single 
largest cause of occupational fatalities causing about 2100 
jobrelated deaths a year 
