a house democrat suggested thursday that a 
10000 donation to the republicans by a business partner of 
president bushs son could have been aimed at blocking an 
investigation concerning a colorado savings and loan association 
the partner dismissed the allegation as total unadulterated 
nonsense and the no 2 house republican said a separate 
democratic move toward requesting a special prosecutor for the 
sampls collapse had the stench of corruption and hypocrisy 
in a day of charges and countercharges concerning the 
institution where neil bush was a director rep frank annunzio of 
illinois suggested developer kenneth m goods 10000 contribution 
to the republican national committee on nov 2 1988 could have 
been a donation of hush money 
annunzio who has accused the bush administration of not 
prosecuting savings and loan fraud vigorously didnt provide 
specific evidence to back up his allegations 
meanwhile action as well as talk was escalating in congress on 
the explosive sampl issue and neil bushs role in the collapse of 
silverado banking savings and loan association bush 34 was a 
director of the denver thrift which failed at a cost to taxpayers 
of 1 billion 
democrats on the house judiciary committee are moving to ask 
attorney general dick thornburgh to appoint an independent counsel 
to investigate silverados collapse rep patricia schroeder 
dcolo said thursday 
the case has criminal implications that should be aggressively 
investigated said a letter that had been signed by 11 of the 
committees democrats by thursday night 
the law requires the signature of at least 12 democrats a 
majority of the 21 on the committee to make the request 
the letter sparked an outraged reaction from no 2 house 
republican newt gingrich dga who criticized congressional 
democrats for seeking to investigate the presidents son while 
trying to block past probes of democrats accused of wrongdoing 
republicans have said democrats are trying to use the neil bush 
case as a way of attacking his father 
the democrats letter to thornburgh said that because neil bush 
and several other people with political connections were associated 
with the bank it would be a conflict of interest for the justice 
department itself to conduct the investigation of silverado 
thornburgh in a news conference wednesday said i am not a 
great fan of independent counsels as you know but we know our 
obligations under the law and will execute them 
a spokesman said that if legislators formally requested a 
special prosecutor he would review the request and respond within 
30 days 
good in a statement issued by his attorney said my 
contribution to the republican party in 1988 was two years after my 
relationship with silverado was terminated through a negotiated 
settlement 
with no evidence whatsoever mr annunzio has accused a 
private citizen of criminal activity he is spreading vicious 
false accusations in the public arena without any basis no 
government agency at any level has accused me of any wrongdoing 
good said 
good donated more than 90000 to republican candidates in the 
198788 period including 5750 for george bushs presidential 
bid the federal election commission said some 85000 to 
candidates other than bush was given in november 1988 just before 
the elections 
the developer who also invested over 3 million in neil bushs 
oil exploration company was the fifthlargest individual political 
contributor in colorado in 1988 according to a study by the center 
for responsive politics 
his contributions included 750 in august 1986 and 5000 in 
october 1987 for the bush presidential campaign said scott moxley 
a spokesman for the federal election commission 
the developer also contributed to the campaigns of several 
democrats including sen robert kerrey of nebraska 500 sen 
timothy e wirth of colorado 2000 and sen george j mitchell 
of maine 500 according to the federal election commission 
during neil bushs tenure on its board silverado loaned good 
around 30 million that was never repaid federal regulators have 
ordered the presidents son to answer allegations of conflict of 
interest in his role as a director of the thrift 
among accusations the regulators allege that he failed to 
adequately disclose his ties to good bush has denied any 
wrongdoing and the president has defended the honor and 
integrity of his son at news conferences 
annunzio said goods donation to the republicans made shortly 
before the election that brought george bush to the white house 
could have been aimed at blocking a justice department 
investigation of good as a silverado borrower 
annunzio said officials of the office of thrift supervision made 
five criminal referrals concerning silverado to the justice 
department but the thrift office has refused to give him the names 
or dates of those referrals 
he speculated that one of the referrals could have involved 
good and that the information is not being made public because the 
referrals could have been made at around the same time good 
contributed the 10000 
annunzio sent a letter thursday to thornburgh requesting copies 
of the five silverado referrals 
justice department spokesman doug tillett said thursday the 
names of any people who might be involved wouldnt be made public 
since they would be part of a pending investigation he wouldnt 
confirm whether silverado referrals had been made to the department 
neil bushs attorney james nesland said his client would have 
no comment 
