<TEXT>
former gov evan mecham can run for office again 
despite his 1988 impeachment and ouster from office the arizona 
supreme court ruled thursday 
impeachment essentially a political process is not subject 
to judicial review the states highest court said in a unanimous 
decision any appeal from the impeachment conviction lies in the 
electoral process 
a former highway patrolman dennis ingram challenged mechams 
reelection bid saying the arizona constitution automatically 
barred him from running again 
the justices decided 50 that the state constitution was 
unclear on that point and that election the ultimate weapon of 
democracy is favored where any doubt exists 
mecham was convicted of misuse of about 80000 given him by 
supporters and obstruction of justice in a coverup of an alleged 
death threat made by an aide 
as expected the court made the only decision that we could 
see that they could make mecham said at a campaign stop in yuma 
we appreciate that and now lets get on with the election and let 
the people do the choosing of who their next governors going to be 
and get on with solving the critical problems of the state 
mecham filed as a gubernatorial candidate last month for the 
sept 11 republican primary he faces four primary opponents 
with incumbent gov rose mofford stepping down the 
gubernatorial race is wide open former phoenix mayor terry goddard 
is considered the democratic frontrunner 
ingram contended mechams impeachment and conviction 
automatically barred mecham from ever again seeking office 
im disappointed obviously said michael meehan ingrams 
lawyer 
mecham argued the state constitution does not automatically ban 
him from seeking public office and the state senate rejected such a 
ban 
the senate convicted mecham by a twothirds vote but came up 
three votes short of a twothirds majority when it considered a 
dracula clause which would have banned him from holding public 
office 
mecham and arizona attorney general bob corbin said 
disqualification from holding office is discretionary and the only 
thing the constitution required was removal from office 
ingram has declined to discuss his motivation for filing the 
challenge to mechams comeback attempt 
mecham has said he believes one of his political opponents was 
behind ingrams challenge but meehan denied that 
