sitting down to talk about deficit reduction the peace dividend 
was peace 
such talk aside the peace dividend continues to crop up on 
campaign trails in places like connecticut iowa colorado and 
nebraska 
josie heath a democratic senate candidate in colorado visited 
with coal miners coming off the morning shift one day last week 
i was telling them id like to cut the defense budget by 50 
percent and they were shaking their heads and saying its about 
time heath said 
she and delauro who is seeking the democratic nomination for an 
open house seat are suggesting similar peace dividend plans that 
would divide military savings between deficit reduction and 
domestic needs such as education health care housing subsidies 
pollution cleanup road and bridge repair and aid to 
defensedependent states and communities 
neither candidate believes peace dividend savings automatically 
must go to the sampl bailout 
i dont think we need to accept rostenkowskis dictum on 
that said delauro we have to decide what it is we want to do 
