anonymity that i do not believe has occurred to date 
the administration is counting on the talks to lower trade 
barriers and greatly expand opportunities for american farmers and 
businesses abroad the aim is to help narrow americas 100 
billionplus trade deficits 
the negotiations which began in uruguay in 1986 face a july 23 
bargaining session in geneva to draft basic agreements in 15 
separate areas including agriculture 
those outlines will then be used over the next five months to 
achieve a final deal by the december deadline 
looking ahead at the schedule the senior american official 
