the us dollar closed mostly firmer in european 
trading on thursday 
gold prices moved lower 
foreign exchange dealers said the dollar traded higher for most 
of the day until some selling shortly before the close 
dealers said the dollar was on the rise because the houston 
summit of the seven major industrialized nations issued no 
statements indicating support for a stronger japanese yen when the 
conference closed on wednesday 
the british pound closed higher despite a day of speculation 
about criticism of west germany france and the european economic 
community by trade and industry secretary nicholas ridley 
the pound fell when ridleys remarks in a magazine interview 
