armand hammer chairman of occidental 
petroleum corp has been sued for 700 million in damages by the 
estate of his late wife frances which claims at least a half 
interest in hammers art collection 
the 18count suit filed wednesday in a los angeles court 
alleges fraud legal malpractice and financial misconduct it 
contends hammer and a law firm representing the industrialist 
repeatedly deceived frances hammer about her ownership rights to 
hammers assets 
the lawsuit was filed by robert weiss of los angeles husband of 
joan weiss mrs weiss is a niece of frances hammer and sole heir 
to her estate mrs hammer died in december after 33 years of 
marriage to armand hammer and named robert weiss executor of her 
will 
the 92yearold hammer maintains that his wife signed documents 
waiving her interest in his art collection which has been 
estimated to be worth 450 million 
richard c cleary a lawyer for the weisses said those signings 
were part of the pattern of fraud and deceit the suit also says 
mrs hammer was fraudulently deprived an interest in thousands of 
shares of occidental stock and millions of dollars in cash paid to 
armand hammer in salary and fringe benefits 
howard collins a spokesman for hammer and occidental declined 
comment on the lawsuit 
also named as defendants are occidental the armand hammer 
foundation lewis overbeck and furman a chicago law firm and the 
armand hammer museum of art and cultural center in los angeles 
where hammers art collection is to be housed 
the lawsuit was the fourth filed in connection with the museum 
which is under construction beside occidentals headquarters 
the others were filed by occidental shareholders seeking to halt 
the companys involvement with the museum occidental has committed 
about 100 million to building and endowing the facility money 
hammer maintains is wellspent because it promotes the corporation 
and will provide a public service 
hammer began collecting art during the 1920s in the soviet 
union his collection including impressionist and old master 
paintings and drawings by leonardo da vinci had been promised to 
the los angeles county museum of art 
but he got into a dispute with that museum over how the art was 
to be displayed and instead decided to build his own museum and 
donate the art to it 
