<TEXT>
assets of the nations 512 money market mutual 
funds rose 310 billion in the latest week to 38583 billion the 
investment company institute said thursday 
the rise in the sevenday period ended wednesday followed a 
220 billion drop in fund assets the week earlier that decline 
originally was reported as 224 billion but the washingtonbased 
mutual fund trade group revised it 
fund assets hit a record high 39214 billion in the week ended 
march 21 the investment company institute said that in the latest 
week assets of 250 general purpose funds rose 7635 million to 
13398 billion assets of 102 brokerdealer funds increased 212 
billion to 16004 billion and assets of 160 institutional funds 
rose 2154 million to 9182 billion 
the sevenday average yield on money market mutual funds fell in 
the week ended tuesday to 765 percent from 768 percent the 
previous week said donoghues money fund report a trade journal 
based in holliston mass 
the 30day average yield remained unchanged at 767 percent 
donoghues said 
the average maturity of the portfolios held by money funds was 
43 days down from 45 days donoghues said 
the newsletter bank rate monitor said its survey of 100 leading 
commercial banks savings and loan associations and savings banks 
in the nations 10 largest markets showed the effective annual 
yield available on money market accounts fell to 614 percent as of 
wednesday from 616 percent a week earlier the north palm beach 
flabased newsletter said the effective annual yield available on 
